  schema:name "Catuṣkoṭi" ;
  schema:description "The four-cornered logical structure in which a proposition may be affirmed, denied, both affirmed and denied, or neither — deployed by Nāgārjuna to demonstrate that all phenomena are empty of inherent existence." ;
